mpqx
-----------
This command line tool can extract files enclosed in MPQ archives. StormLib
is used to parse/extract MPQ archive. 

Command syntax listed as below:

    Usage: mpqx [options] <MPQ Archive>
                 options: -a extract all files in archive
                          -p <pattern>
                             extract only files whos full path match the
                             <pattern>. Wildcast '?' and '*' can be used.
                          -l list all files in the archive
                          -L <listfile>
                             supply additional listfile

    Do nothing if no option is given.

Tested under Mac OS X 10.8.2, StormLib 8.20.

blp2bmp
-----------
This command line tool can convert textures enclosed in BLP files (Blizzard's 
texture format) into ordinary 32bpp BMP image. DXT1/3/5 compression methods 
are supported.

Command syntax listed as below:

    Usage: blp2bmp [-i | -a] <blp_file>
           -i      dump blp2 header
	       -a      convert all mipmaps

Tested under Mac OS X 10.8.2, this program can convert Interface/ICONS/*.blp
textures inflated from Data/interface.MPQ, World of Warcraft r16057.

